<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-179-891  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 179 891.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DG Review  July 1990 v11 n1 pS1(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fast, flexible FDDI. (Fiber Distributed Data Interface)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goodloe, Tony.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>FDDI is becoming the local area network (LAN) standard.andP;  It hasseveral advantages over Ethernet: virtual immunity to electricalinterface and better security because it is difficult to eavesdropon an optical fiber.andP;  It specifies a ring network ofpoint-to-point fiber-optic connections.andP;  A token-passing schemecontrols access to the network.andP;  FDDI can act on all three networktypes: front-end, back-end, and backbone.andP;  FDDI's fast,fiber-optic LAN technology should fulfill the demand for greaterbandwidth.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksFiber Distributed Data Interface StandardFiber OpticsEthernetBandwidth.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   FDDI works in every network type. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>